{
  "stem": "7458.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then we went to Bialystok, where my cousin actually got us an apartment above a police station so that we would be safe.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the family stayed there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But we decided that we could never live in Poland again, there would never be a life for us in Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We couldn't live-- even if they stopped killing us, we couldn't live on the graves of our beloved.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We didn't know where they were buried.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They were buried here, there, and everywhere, wherever they were shot and killed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we decided that my brother Maishe and I would be the first ones to leave and to go and see if there is  a way to get out of Poland and go to Israel, to Palestine at that time.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So more or less on foot and by truck and on trains, whatever we could get a hold of, we went from country to country.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We ended up going through Czechoslovakia and Hungary and Austria.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And eventually we ended up in Italy, where the Israeli Haganah sent in people to help and take people to Israel.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You might recall that England did not allow movement of Jews to Israel at that time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the days-- those were the days of-- of the ship exodus.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And eventually, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my brother stayed in Italy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We settled in displaced persons' camps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were several of them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One of them was-- they were all in southern Italy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Italy is shaped like a boot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the camp where we were was right here at the heel of the-- the heel of the boot, called Santa Cesarea.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was also another camp a couple miles away, Santa Maria di Leuca.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
